external_knowledge:
- The term "stands tall" refers to being the best or most prominent in a particular context;
- "Champion" is a metaphor for the team with the highest number of wins;
- "Victorious matches" refers to the matches won by the team.

- "fledgling teams" refers to teams founded after 2010;
- "grown to include more than 10 players" refers to teams with more than 10 players;
- "more than one branch" means there are multiple entries for the same team name in different cities;
- "inception" refers to the founding year of the team.

sql:
SELECT AVG(match_count) AS average_matches_per_city
FROM (
  SELECT city_id, COUNT(match_id) AS match_count
  FROM matches
  GROUP BY city_id
);

